==Personal life==
Memphis is a [[Christianity|Christian]]. He became a Christian in 2016. During the 2022 FIFA World Cup, Memphis led a [[Bible study (Christianity)|Bible study]] with his teammate [[Cody Gakpo]] for 15 other Netherlands players.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wise |first1=Talia |title=Dutch Stars Depay, Gakpo Stand for Christ During FIFA World Cup: 'We Are Thankful to God' |date=9 December 2022 |url=https://www1.cbn.com/cbnnews/world/2022/december/dutch-stars-depay-gakpo-stand-for-christ-during-fifa-world-cup-we-are-thankful-to-god |access-date=13 January 2023}}</ref>

Memphis has numerous tattoos, including one on his left arm that is a tribute to his grandfather, who died on the day before he turned 15.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Memphis Depay on Louis van Gaal and winning the Premier League |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33631715 |publisher=BBC Sport (British Broadcasting Corporation) |date=23 July 2015 |access-date=23 July 2015}}</ref> When he scored against Australia at the 2014 World Cup, he kissed this tattoo and pointed to the sky, dedicating his goal to his late grandfather, a moment which he then in 2016 commemorated with a tattoo on his left torso depicting [[Christ the Redeemer (statue)|Christ the Redeemer]] and the date 18.06.14, referring to his first international goal for the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Memphis Depay showt zijn tattoo met speciale betekenis |date=7 August 2016 |url=http://www.soccernews.nl/news/363470/Memphis_Depay_showt_zijn_tattoo_met_speciale_betekenis|access-date=13 August 2016}}</ref> He also has a tattoo on the inside of his lip stating ''succesvol'' (which is Dutch for 'successful')<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/prive/21576789/__Bizarre_tattoo_voor_PSV_er_Memphis__.html |title=Bizarre tattoo voor PSV'er Memphis |newspaper=[[De Telegraaf]] |date=18 May 2013|access-date=13 August 2016}}</ref> and also has the words 'dream chaser' emblazoned on his upper torso.<ref name="things">{{Cite web |title=Manchester United's new signing Memphis Depay – eight things you should know |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfers/11551546/Manchester-United-Liverpool-and-Arsenal-target-Memphis-Depay-eight-things-you-should-know.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfers/11551546/Manchester-United-Liverpool-and-Arsenal-target-Memphis-Depay-eight-things-you-should-know.html |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |date=6 May 2015 |work=The Daily Telegraph|access-date=4 October 2015}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

In June 2017, it was announced on social media that Memphis was engaged to [[Lori Harvey]], the youngest daughter of American television personality [[Steve Harvey]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Memphis Depay's Engagement to Steve Harvey's Daughter Lori Announced |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2718122-memphis-depays-engagement-to-steve-harveys-daughter-lori-announced |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |date=26 June 2017|access-date=27 June 2017 |first=Tom |last=Sunderland}}</ref> Since then, they have ended their engagement and relationship.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lori Harvey, Steve Harvey's Step Daughter, Kisses Up on Trey Songz in the Club |url=https://madamenoire.com/1053372/lori-harvey-steve-harveys-step-daughter-kisses-up-on-trey-songz-in-the-club |publisher=Madamenoire |date=24 December 2018|access-date=3 June 2019}}</ref>

In April 2020, Memphis was criticised by several animal rights organisations for posting pictures of himself with a [[liger]] cub while on vacation in [[Dubai]]. He responded by stating that "ligers are not even wild animals".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Animal rights groups blast Depay's big cat pics |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lyon/story/4082973/memphis-depays-baby-big-cat-pics-on-blast-by-animal-rights-groups |date=6 April 2020 |website=ESPN.com|access-date=6 May 2020}}</ref>

In June 2022, Memphis visited Ghana<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 June 2022 |title=Watch how Memphis Depay arrived in Ghana for his summer holidays |url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Watch-how-Memphis-Depay-arrived-in-Ghana-for-his-summer-holidays-1562246 |access-date=19 June 2022 |website=GhanaWeb |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ayamga |first=Emmanuel |date=16 June 2022 |title=Video: Barcelona superstar Memphis Depay arrives in Ghana for holidays |url=https://www.pulse.com.gh/sports/football/barcelona-superstar-memphis-depay-arrives-in-ghana-for-holidays-video/72t50l4 |access-date=19 June 2022 |website=Pulse Ghana |language=en |archive-date=19 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220619003300/https://www.pulse.com.gh/sports/football/barcelona-superstar-memphis-depay-arrives-in-ghana-for-holidays-video/72t50l4 |url-status=dead }}</ref> where he undertook some philanthropic works in the Cape Coast School of the Deaf and Blind.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 June 2022 |title=Barcelona forward, Memphis Depay, refurbishes Cape Coast School for Deaf and Blind - MyJoyOnline.com |url=https://www.myjoyonline.com/barcelona-forward-memphis-depay-refurbishes-cape-coast-school-for-deaf-and-blind/ |access-date=19 June 2022 |website=www.myjoyonline.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

